# =============================================================================
# .gitignore  —  ppg-microvascular-feasibility-mimic (PUBLIC repo)
# =============================================================================
# This is a public-bound repository. Anything credentialed, secret, derived,
# or internal-process MUST stay out of every commit. When in doubt, ignore it.
# Audit every staged file before the first public push.
# =============================================================================

# ---- credentialed data: NEVER commit (PhysioNet DUA) ----
# Ignore directory CONTENTS (data/*, not data/) so git can still descend and
# honor the README negation below. A trailing-slash ignore would block descent
# and the negation would never fire.
data/*
!data/README.md
*.parquet
*.csv.gz
*.hea
*.dat
*.wfdb

# ---- secrets: NEVER commit ----
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.key
*.pem
id_rsa
id_rsa.*
secrets.*
*_api_key*
*credentials*

# ---- agent / MCP / tooling config (never public) ----
.claude/
.mcp.json
**/.mcp.json

# ---- model weights: never ship (users pull MedGemma themselves) ----
*.safetensors
*.gguf
*.bin
*.pt
models/

# ---- derived results: ship only curated public/aggregate outputs ----
# Ignore directory CONTENTS (results/*, not results/) so the README negation
# can fire. Never commit row-level PHI or private subtrees.
results/*
!results/README.md
results/private/
results/**/*_raw*.csv

# ---- archived null artifacts: keep on disk, never push ----
**/_archive_v1_null/

# ---- run-time logs (may contain absolute home paths in error traces) ----
logs/
*.log

# ---- python / tooling ----
.venv/
__pycache__/
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc
.ipynb_checkpoints/
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.coverage
dist/
build/
*.egg-info/

# ---- LaTeX build artifacts (the manuscript .tex is tracked; outputs are not) ----
*.aux
*.bbl
*.blg
*.fdb_latexmk
*.fls
*.lof
*.lot
*.out
*.synctex.gz
*.toc
manuscript/tex/*.log
manuscript/tex/*.pdf

# ---- internal planning / process files: NEVER commit to the public repo ----
# These are working notes and evidence workbooks, not release artifacts.
# (.gitattributes export-ignore only affects archives, not `git add`; ignore here too.)
task_plan.md
findings.md
progress.md
HANDOFF.md
findings/
manuscript/workbooks/

# ---- Internal docs and agent config -- held from public release ----
# The entire docs/ tree (00 charter through 04 release inventory) is an internal
# process record, not a release artifact. CLAUDE.md is agent-orchestration config.
# manuscript/refs/ contains only an internal citation QA log.
docs/
CLAUDE.md
manuscript/refs/
# Figure build docs are internal working notes (carry subject pseudonyms + stale
# jargon); the figures themselves ship, these build records do not.
manuscript/figures/buildlog.md
manuscript/figures/captions.md
# Internal HTML deliverables (work summary, repo preview) for the author, not the release.
reports/

# ---- release tooling (private; hardcodes absolute paths) ----
release_tooling/

# ---- manuscript layout variants (working artifacts; only the chosen manuscript.tex ships) ----
manuscript/layouts/

# ---- OS / IDE / editor cruft ----
.DS_Store
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
